---
import SimpleLayout from '../layouts/SimpleLayout.astro';
---
<SimpleLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

  <p>Last updated: April 2026</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>The Climate Finance Wiki is a static documentation site published by Red Barrow. This site does not collect personal data, require account creation, or use cookies for tracking purposes.</p>

  <h2>Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
  <p>This site does not collect, store, or process any personally identifiable information. There are no sign-up forms, login systems, comment sections, or analytics trackers embedded in the site. We do not use advertising cookies, retargeting pixels, or third-party data brokers.</p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>This site loads web fonts from Google Fonts. Google may collect anonymised usage data as part of its font delivery service. For details, see <a href="https://developers.google.com/fonts/faq/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Fonts Privacy FAQ</a>.</p>
  <p>Images may be served from external sources such as Unsplash. These services have their own privacy policies governing how they process requests.</p>

  <h2>Hosting</h2>
  <p>This site is hosted as a static site. The hosting provider may collect standard server logs including IP addresses, browser type, and request timestamps. These logs are used solely for infrastructure monitoring and security purposes and are not shared with third parties.</p>

  <h2>External Links</h2>
  <p>Articles on this wiki link to external sources such as UNFCCC documents, EU Commission publications, SEC filings, and academic papers. These external sites have their own privacy policies. We are not responsible for the content or privacy practices of linked sites.</p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>This site is a professional reference tool and is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children.</p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>If the site's data practices change, this policy will be updated with a new "Last updated" date. Since this is a static site with no data collection, changes are unlikely.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>For questions about this privacy policy, contact us via the details on the <a href="/about/#contact">About page</a>.</p>
</SimpleLayout>
